                                  "name": "smNarrative",
                                  "fill": "$font-primary",
                                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                  "width": "fill_container",
                                  "content": "A 47-year-old Kenyan woman died at home in Nyeri County following a two-week illness. She had been diagnosed with HIV one year prior and was inconsistent with antiretroviral therapy. Progressive symptoms included a dry, productive cough that became blood-tinged, right-sided pleuritic chest pain, drenching night sweats, and progressive weight loss. No prior TB treatment history was reported. The clinical pattern — active pulmonary involvement in an untreated HIV-positive adult — is most consistent with pulmonary tuberculosis as an opportunistic infection, and the ACME decision table identifies HIV as the underlying cause in this causal chain.",
